CHANGES: REPO-KEEP                                                 2.0
=======================================================================

2.0   (X. September 2011)
This release is a complete rewrite of repo-update. The naming of the executable
has been changed to just repo, the project has been renamed repo-keep, the
programming language has been changed to C, and many improvements have been
made to the concept (hence the name change).

Enhancements:
  - Available commands: sync, update, add, remove
  - See help for options

_______________________________
1.4.1 (20. April 2011)
This release just adds a Zsh completion script for repo-update,
and does not change the functionality of repo-update at all.

Enhancements:
  - Added a Zsh completion script.

